# PeaNUT Project Overview

PeaNUT is a Tiny Dashboard for Network UPS Tools (NUT) - a Next.js web application for monitoring UPS devices connected to your network.

## Project Structure

- **Entry Point**: [src/app/layout.tsx](mdc:src/app/layout.tsx) - Main app layout
- **Configuration**: [package.json](mdc:package.json) - Dependencies and scripts
- **TypeScript Config**: [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json) - TypeScript configuration with path aliases
- **Testing**: [jest.config.ts](mdc:jest.config.ts) - Jest configuration for unit and e2e tests
- **Linting**: [eslint.config.mjs](mdc:eslint.config.mjs) - ESLint configuration

## Key Directories

- `src/app/` - Next.js App Router pages and API routes
- `src/client/` - React components and client-side logic
- `src/server/` - Server-side utilities and NUT integration
- `src/common/` - Shared types and constants
- `__tests__/` - Test files (unit and e2e)
- `config/` - Configuration files for NUT and UPS devices

## Tech Stack

- **Framework**: Next.js 15 with App Router
- **Language**: TypeScript
- **UI**: React 19, Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui components (Radix UI primitives)
- **State Management**: TanStack Query (React Query)
- **Authentication**: NextAuth.js
- **Testing**: Jest, React Testing Library, Playwright
- **Monitoring**: InfluxDB, Prometheus integration
- **Package Manager**: pnpm

## Key Features

- Real-time UPS monitoring via NUT protocol
- Customizable dashboard with drag-and-drop widgets
- API access for external integrations
- Terminal access to NUT servers
- Multi-language support (i18n)
- Dark/light theme support
- Comprehensive testing suite
